The paper proposes an ontology-based approach for human-centric explanation of transfer learning, which involves utilizing knowledge from one learning domain to enhance prediction model training in another learning domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of external knowledge bases and ontologies, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Knowledge Representation and Reasoning (cs.KR). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of its proposed approach using real-world data, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
